# Backend Lifecycle — Check Before, Restart After

The visualizer backend runs on **port 5001** via:
```bash
cd /Users/ccanales/projects/lightroom-tagger/apps/visualizer/backend
/Users/ccanales/projects/lightroom-tagger/.venv/bin/python app.py >> /tmp/backend.log 2>&1 &
```

## Before making any backend changes

Check whether the backend is currently running:
```bash
lsof -iTCP:5001 -sTCP:LISTEN -P -n 2>/dev/null | awk 'NR>1 {print $2}'
```

Save the result. If a PID is returned, the backend **is live** — note it so you can restart after changes.

## After making backend changes

If the backend was running before your changes, restart it:
```bash
# Kill the old process
lsof -iTCP:5001 -sTCP:LISTEN -P -n 2>/dev/null | awk 'NR>1 {print $2}' | sort -u | xargs kill 2>/dev/null
sleep 1
# Start fresh
cd /Users/ccanales/projects/lightroom-tagger/apps/visualizer/backend
/Users/ccanales/projects/lightroom-tagger/.venv/bin/python app.py >> /tmp/backend.log 2>&1 &
echo "Backend restarted (PID $!)"
```

Then confirm it came up:
```bash
sleep 2 && curl -s http://localhost:5001/api/jobs/ | python3 -c "import sys,json; json.load(sys.stdin); print('Backend OK')" 2>/dev/null || echo "Backend not responding yet"
```

## Rules

- **Never leave the backend dead** after a change session. If it was up when you started, it must be up when you finish.
- **Never kill the backend** without immediately restarting it (unless the user explicitly asks to stop it).
- **If the backend was not running** before your changes, leave it stopped — don't start it uninvited.
- This applies to changes in: `apps/visualizer/backend/`, `lightroom_tagger/core/`, `apps/visualizer/backend/jobs/`, `apps/visualizer/backend/api/`.
